      "text": [
        ": «إِنِّي لآَخُذُ مِنْ أَحَدِكُمُ اَلدِّرْهَمَ وَ إِنِّي لَمِنْ أَكْثَرِ أَهْلِ اَلْمَدِينَةِ مَالاً مَا أُرِيدُ بِذَلِكَ إِلاَّ أَنْ تُطَهَّرُوا »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1658 - Abdullah ibn Bukayr narrated from Abu Abdullah Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) who said:\n\"I take a dirham from one of you, while I am among the wealthiest people in Medina. I do this only so that you may be purified.\""
        ]
